org.matsim.pt.router

Class TransitRouterNetwork.TransitRouterNetworkLink

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.matsim.pt.router.TransitRouterNetwork.TransitRouterNetworkLink
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    BasicLocation<Link>, Identifiable<Link>, Link, Attributable
    Enclosing class:
    TransitRouterNetwork

    public static final class TransitRouterNetwork.TransitRouterNetworkLink
extends Object
implements Link
    Looks to me like an implementation of the Link interface, with get(Transit)Route and get(Transit)Line on top. To recall: TransitLine is something like M44. But it can have more than one route, e.g. going north, going south, long route, short route. That is, presumably we have one such TransitRouterNetworkLink per TransitRoute. kai/manuel, feb'12
